 />\n|-\n| 2019\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Party (upcoming film)|Party]]''\n| \"Cha Cha Charey\"\n| Tamil\n| Co-sang with [[Karthi]], [[Kharesma Ravichandran]], [[Venkat Prabhu]] and [[Premgi Amaren]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/cha-cha-charey-from-party-single/1406698225 |title=Cha Cha Charey (From \"Party\")&nbsp;\u2013 Single |date=2 July 2018 |website=[[Apple Music]] |publisher=[[Muzik 247]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180920141643/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/cha-cha-charey-from-party-single/1406698225 |archive-date=20 September 2018 |access-date=20 September 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Soorarai Pottru]]''\n| \"Maara Theme\"\n| Tamil\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/others/soorarai-pottrus-all-new-song-maara-theme-is-out-now.html |title=Soorarai Pottru's All New Song Maara Theme Is Out Now, Here Is All You Need To Know |date=24 January 2020 |website=Republic World |access-date=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020\n! scope=\"row\" |''Aakaasam Nee Haddhu Ra''\n| \"Maha Theme\"\n| Telugu\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/maha-theme-telugu-from-aakaasam-nee-haddhu-ra/1496304606 |title=Maha Theme (Telugu) [From \"Aakaasam Nee Haddhu Ra\"] \u2013 Single |date=24 January 2020 |website=[[Apple Music]] |url-status=live |archive-url=http://archive.today/gZlVt |archive-date=26 March 2020 |access-date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== Music video appearances ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" id=\"filmography\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Role(s)\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Performer(s)\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Tooltip|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| 2017\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Maatrangal Ondre Dhaan''\n| Himself\n|{{sort|Prasanna|Nivas K. Prasanna}}\n| Promotional song for the film ''[[Kootathil Oruthan]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oE6zm6OAghg |title=Maatrangal Ondre Dhaan ( Gift Song ) Feat. Nivas K Prasanna |date=20 June 2017 |language=Tamil |publisher=[[Think Music India]] |place=India |access-date=24 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724083230/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oE6zm6OAghg |archive-date=24 July 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Short films ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role(s)\n! Director\n! Language\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|{{Tooltip|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| 2008\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Herova? Zerova?]]'' \n| Himself\n| [[V. Priya]]\n| Tamil\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200805162223.htm |title=TN actors in documentary highlighting evils of child labour |date=16 May 2008 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=10 February 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604120118/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200805162223.htm |archive-date=4 June 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n* [[List of awards and nominations received by Suriya]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|name=Suriya filmography|id=1421814}}\n\n{{featured list}}\n\n[[Category:Actor filmographies]]\n[[Category:Indian filmographies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2017}}\n[[File:Suriya at Inam screening.jpg|thumb|alt=Suriya in a dark, long-sleeved shirt posing for the camera|[[Suriya]] at the premiere of ''[[Ceylon (film)|Ceylon]]'' in 2014]]\n[[Suriya]] is an Indian film actor and producer who works primarily in [[Tamil cinema]]. He made a commercially successful cinematic debut in [[Vasanth]]'s ''[[Nerrukku Ner]]'' (1997).<ref name=\"Landmark\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-looking-at-suriyas-landmark-films/20111020.htm |title=Looking at Suriya's landmark films |last=Srinivasan |first=Pavithra |date=20 October 2011 |website=[[Rediff.com]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170115114925/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-looking-at-suriyas-landmark-films/20111020.htm |archive-date=15 January 2017 |access-date=15 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2008/nov/11sli1.htm |title=The best of Surya |last=Srinivasan |first=Pavithra |date=11 November 2008 |website=Rediff.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116144226/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2008/nov/11sli1.htm |archive-date=16 January 2017 |access-date=13 January 2017}}</ref> This was followed by roles in a series of critical and commercial failures, including ''[[Kaadhale Nimmadhi]]'' (1998), ''[[Sandhippoma]]'' (1998) and ''[[Periyanna]]'' (1999).<ref>{{Cite news |last=Rangarajan |first=Malathi |url=http://www.thehindu.com/2000/06/09/stories/09090224.htm |title=Each step is a measured one |date=9 June 2000 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=16 January 2017 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116123648/http://www.thehindu.com/2000/06/09/stories/09090224.htm |archive-date=16 January 2017}}</ref> Suriya collaborated with Vasanth again in ''[[Poovellam Kettuppar]]'' (1999), his first film with future wife [[Jyothika]].<ref name=\"Landmark\" /><ref name=\"Talk\">{{Cite news |last=Kamath |first=Sudhish |url=http://www.thehindu.com/2001/07/11/stories/0411401v.htm |title=Talk of the Town |date=11 July 2001 |work=The Hindu |access-date=16 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116123338/http://www.thehindu.com/2001/07/11/stories/0411401v.htm |archive-date=16 January 2017 |last2=Shankar |first2=T.S. |last3=Radhakrishnan |first3=R.K. |author-link=Sudhish Kamath}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, Suriya starred in [[Bala (director)|Bala]]'s ''[[Nandha]]'' as an ex-convict trying to find his place in society.<ref name=\"NamanOutlook\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/singam-on-song/286838 |title=Singam On Song |last=Ramachandran |first=Naman |authorlink=Naman Ramachandran |date=22 July 2013 |website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117161035/http://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/singam-on-song/286838 |archive-date=17 January 2017 |access-date=17 January 2017}}</ref> The film was critically acclaimed and became a turning point in his career.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pillai |first=Sreedhar |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/07/24/stories/2002072400140200.htm |title=A chip off the old block |date=24 July 2002 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117083719/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/07/24/stories/2002072400140200.htm |archive-date=17 January 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"CNN5\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/happy-birthday-suriya-5-performances-that-make-him-the-singam-of-tamil-cinema-1024604.html |title=Happy Birthday Suriya: 5 performances that make him the 'Singam' of Tamil cinema |last=Rajpal |first=Roktim |date=23 July 2015 |website=[[CNN-News18]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117083853/http://www.news18.com/news/movies/18-years-of-suriya-how-a-garment-factory-worker-turned-into-the-most-bankable-tamil-star-1079969.html |archive-date=17 January 2017 |access-date=17 January 2017}}</ref> His roles as a police in [[Gautham Menon]]'s 2003 [[action film]] ''[[Kaakha Kaakha]]'' and a [[Confidence trick|con man]] in Bala's drama, ''[[Pithamagan]]'' (2003), established him as one of Tamil cinema's leading actors.<ref name=\"Landmark\" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Pillai |first=Sreedhar |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/12/29/stories/2003122900170100.htm |title=Reel of fortune |date=29 December 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117085958/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/12/29/stories/2003122900170100.htm |archive-date=17 January 2017}}</ref> Suriya's performances in both films were praised, winning him a [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Actor]] nomination for the former and the [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Supporting Actor]] for ''Pithamagan'' at the [[51st Filmfare Awards South]].<ref name=\"Filmfare2003\">{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/51st-Annual-Manikchand-Filmfare-Award-winners/articleshow/718496.cms |title=51st Annual Manikchand Filmfare Award winners |date=4 June 2004 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.is/20150126140422/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/51st-Annual-Manikchand-Filmfare-Award-winners/articleshow/718496.cms |archive-date=26 January 2015}}</ref> The following year, he played [[dual role]]s\u2014a hunchback and a college student\u2014in ''[[Perazhagan]]''. Suriya's performance was again praised, and he received his first [[52nd Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Best Actor award]].<ref name=\"NamanOutlook\" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Surendran |first=Anusha |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/entertainment/twice-as-nice/article8488429.ece |title=Twice as nice |date=18 April 2016 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305081344/http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/entertainment/twice-as-nice/article8488429.ece |archive-date=5 March 2017}}</ref> He was also acclaimed for his performance as a student leader in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s ''[[Aaytha Ezhuthu]]'' (2004).<ref name=\"NamanOutlook\" />\n\nIn 2005, Suriya starred in three films: ''[[Maayavi]]'', ''[[Ghajini (2005 film)|Ghajini]]'' and ''[[Aaru (film)|Aaru]]''. His performance in ''Ghajini'' as a businessman with [[anterograde amnesia]] was widely praised.<ref name=\"CNN5\" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Pillai |first=Sreedhar |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2005/12/30/stories/2005123001140100.htm |title=Tamil cinema's new high |date=30 December 2005 |work=The Hindu |access-date=19 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141004052839/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2005/12/30/stories/2005123001140100.htm |archive-date=4 October 2014}}</ref> ''Maayavi'' and ''Aaru'' were moderately successful.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=plupk4hgbcbec |title=Chennai box-office (Mar 25{{ndash}}27) |date=30 March 2005 |website=[[Sify]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119103452/http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=plupk4hgbcbec |archive-date=19 January 2017 |access-date=19 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=plupluegfdhgb |title=Chennai box-office (Jan 06{{ndash}}08) |date=10 January 2006 |website=Sify |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119104939/http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=plupluegfdhgb |archive-date=19 January 2017 |access-date=19 January 2017}}</ref> Over the next two years, Suriya starred in ''[[Sillunu Oru Kaadhal]]'' (2006) and ''[[Vel (film)|Vel]]'' (2007). Although the former was a [[box-office bomb]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=plupmnajhhhhf |title=Chennai box-office(Oct 06{{ndash}}08) |date=10 October 2006 |website=Sify |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119103457/http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=plupmnajhhhhf |archive-date=19 January 2017 |access-date=19 January 2017}}</ref> ''Vel'', where he played twins, was commercially successful.<ref name=\"VelSify\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vel-review-tamil-pclwzbfegcihb.html |title=Vel |date=9 November 2007 |website=Sify |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170115133448/http://www.sify.com/movies/vel-review-tamil-pclwzbfegcihb.html |archive-date=15 January 2017 |access-date=15 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Pillai |first=Sreedhar |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Source=Page&Skin=TOI&BaseHref=TOICH/2008/10/24&PageLabel=25&EntityId=Ar02500&ViewMode=HTML&GZ=T |title=Diwali dampeners |date=24 October 2008 |work=The Times of India |access-date=19 January 2017 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170119104447/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Source=Page&Skin=TOI&BaseHref=TOICH%2F2008%2F10%2F24&PageLabel=25&EntityId=Ar02500&ViewMode=HTML&GZ=T |archive-date=19 January 2017}}</ref> Suriya's next appearance was in the [[romantic drama]], ''[[Vaaranam Aayiram]]'' (2008).<ref name=\"VAMR\">{{Cite news |last=Rangarajan |first=Malathi |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/An-ode-to-dad-dearest-Vaaranam-Aayiram/article15400806.ece |title=An ode to dad dearest&nbsp;\u2014 Vaaranam Aayiram |date=21 November 2008 |work=The Hindu |access-date=15 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170115134248/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/An-ode-to-dad-dearest-Vaaranam-Aayiram/article15400806.ece |archive-date=15 January 2017}}</ref> His dual role as father and son earned him another Filmfare Best Actor award.<ref name=\"Filmfare2008\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/56th-filmfare-awards-2008-given-away-news-tamil-kkfrEufbgecsi.html |title=56th Filmfare Awards 2008 given away |date=3 August 2009 |website=Sify |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119121245/http://www.sify.com/movies/56th-filmfare-awards-2008-given-away-news-tamil-kkfrEufbgecsi.html |archive-date=19 January 2017 |access-date=19 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nSuriya's next three films were ''[[Ayan (film)|Ayan]]'' (2009), ''[[Aadhavan]]'' (2009) and ''[[Singam]]'' (2010). The latter, in which he starred with [[Anushka Shetty]], was his most commercially successful film to date and spawned two sequels: ''[[Singam II]]'' (2013) and ''[[Si3 (film)|Si3]]'' (2017).<ref name=\"Special\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-birthday-special-10-best-films-of-suriya-south/20140723.htm |title=Birthday Special: 10 Best Films of Suriya |last=Saraswathi |first=S |date=23 July 2014 |website=Rediff.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119124913/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-birthday-special-10-best-films-of-suriya-south/20140723.htm |archive-date=19 January 2017 |access-date=19 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/s3-now-becomes-c3-for-tax-exemption-news-tamil-rbrjIWhfheief.html |title=S3 now becomes C3 for tax-exemption! |date=17 January 2017 |website=Sify |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118154617/http://www.sify.com/movies/s3-now-becomes-c3-for-tax-exemption-news-tamil-rbrjIWhfheief.html |archive-date=18 January 2017 |access-date=18 January 2017}}</ref>{{efn|''Singam'' was Suriya's 25th film.<ref name=\"Special\" />}} The actor made his [[Hindi]] and [[Telugu cinema]] debuts in the [[Rakta Charitra 2|second part]] of [[Ram Gopal Varma]]'s [[gangster film]] ''Rakta Charitra'' (2010).<ref name=\"Landmark\" /><ref name=\"Oberoi\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/birthday-special-vivek-oberois-5-memorable-performances/16506199 |title=Birthday special: Vivek Oberoi's 5 memorable performances |date=3 September 2015 |work=[[Mid Day]] |access-date=16 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116100205/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/birthday-special-vivek-oberois-5-memorable-performances/16506199 |archive-date=16 January 2017}}</ref> Suriya then played the [[Bhikkhu|Buddhist monk]] and creator of [[Shaolin Kung Fu]], [[Bodhidharma]], and his fictional descendant Aravind, in ''[[7aum Arivu]]'' (2011).<ref name=\"7Sense\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-seven-am-arivu/20111026.htm |title=Review: 7am Arivu is worth a watch |last=Srinivasan |first=Pavithra |date=26 October 2011 |website=Rediff.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170115162548/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-seven-am-arivu/20111026.htm |archive-date=15 January 2017 |access-date=15 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Parsai |first=Gargi |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/education-will-give-flight-to-girls-anandmurti-gurumaa/article8249133.ece |title='Education will give flight to girls': Anandmurti Gurumaa |date=17 February 2016 |work=The Hindu |access-date=19 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119130850/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/education-will-give-flight-to-girls-anandmurti-gurumaa/article8249133.ece |archive-date=19 January 2017}}</ref> His only 2012 release was ''[[Maattrraan]]'', in which he played [[conjoined twins]].<ref name=\"Maattrraan\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-maattraan-is-not-up-to-the-mark/20121012.htm |title=Review: Maattrraan is not up to the mark |last=Srinivasan |first=Pavithra |date=12 October 2012 |website=Rediff.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170115161957/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-maattraan-is-not-up-to-the-mark/20121012.htm |archive-date=15 January 2017 |access-date=15 January 2017}}</ref> In 2015, Suriya released ''[[36 Vayadhinile]]'', the first film from his [[2D Entertainment]] production company.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Menon |first=Vishal |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/gnanavel-raja-speaks-on-suriyas-24/article8551774.ece |title=\"Suriya has Rs.50 crore market potential in Andhra, Telangana\" |date=3 May 2016 |work=The Hindu |access-date=19 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119131016/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/gnanavel-raja-speaks-on-suriyas-24/article8551774.ece |archive-date=19 January 2017}}</ref> He played three roles for the first time in [[Vikram Kumar]]'s [[science fiction film]], ''[[24 (2016 film)|24]]'' (2016).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/five-reasons-why-you-should-watch-24-news-tamil-qffjX7idahecg.html |title=Five reasons why you should watch 24 |date=5 May 2016 |website=Sify |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119132201/http://www.sify.com/movies/five-reasons-why-you-should-watch-24-news-tamil-qffjX7idahecg.html |archive-date=19 January 2017 |access-date=19 January 2017}}</ref> It became one of the year's highest-grossing Tamil films and his performances earned him a [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor&nbsp;\u2013 South|Critics Award for Best Actor]] at Filmfare.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pillai |first=Sreedhar |url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/Kollywood%E2%80%99s-2016-report-card/article16937524.ece |title=Kollywood\u2019s 2016 report card |date=24 December 2016 |work=The Hindu |access-date=19 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119131702/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/Kollywood%E2%80%99s-2016-report-card/article16937524.ece |archive-date=19 January 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"FF2017\">{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/winners-64th-jio-filmfare-awards-south/articleshow/59192157.cms |title=Winners: 64th Jio Filmfare Awards (South) |date=18 June 2017 |work=The Times of India |access-date=18 June 2017 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6rJ496Tl8?url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/winners-64th-jio-filmfare-awards-south/articleshow/59192157.cms |archive-date=18 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Films ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"|{{Dagger}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n=== As an actor ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" |Year\n! scope=\"col\" |Film\n! scope=\"col\" |Role(s)\n! scope=\"col\" |Director(s)\n! scope=\"col\" |Language(s)\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|{{Tooltip|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| 1997\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Nerrukku Ner]]''\n| Suriya\n| [[Vasanth]]\n|[[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Landmark\" />\n|-\n| 1998\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Kaadhale Nimmadhi]]''\n| Chandru\n| Indiran\n| Tamil\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Filmography\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/filmography-surya-news-tamil-kkfse3egcjcsi.html |title=Filmography: Surya |date=22 April 2009 |website=Sify |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170115121130/http://www.sify.com/movies/filmography-surya-news-tamil-kkfse3egcjcsi.html |archive-date=15 January 2017 |access-date=15 January 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1998\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Sandhippoma]]''\n| Vishwa\n|{{sort|Indrakumar|T. Indrakumar}}\n| Tamil\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Filmography\" />\n|-\n| 1999\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Periyanna]]''\n| Suriya\n|{{sort|Chandrasekhar|[[S. A. Chandrasekhar]]}}\n| Tamil\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Filmography\" /><br /><ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YuykmgtRgoY |title=Periyanna |date=4 January 2013 |type=Motion Picture |language=Tamil |publisher=[[Rajshri Productions|Rajshri Tamil]] |trans-title=Big Brother |access-date=15 January 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1999\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Poovellam Kettuppar]]''\n| Krishna\n|[[Vasanth]]\n| Tamil\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Landmark\" /><br /><ref name=\"Filmography\" />\n|-\n| 2000\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Uyirile Kalanthathu]]''\n| Suriya\n|{{sort|Jaya|K. R. Jaya}}\n| Tamil\n|\n|style=\"text-align:c